HEADWORD: Parieto-
<hw>Pa*ri"e*to-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A combining
form used to indicate <xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation
to</xex>, <xex>the parietal bones or the parietal segment of the
skull</xex>; <as>as, the <ex>parieto</ex>-mastoid suture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parigenin</ent>⟦br⟧
